<module>
    <h>blàth</h>
    <p><g>blàth</g>
        <en>warm</en> is a <a href="?xx=adjectives/simple_adjectives">simple adjective</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Like other (gradable) adjectives, <g>blàth</g> can occur with an intensifying
                pre-specifier like <a href="?gd=glee"><g>glé</g></a>
                <en>very</en>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an seomar <m>glé bhlàth</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The room is very warm.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-pred">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>blàth</g> can be used (uninflected) as the predicate of the verb <a
                    href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an seòmar seo <m>blàth</m>?</gd>
                        <tr>Is this room warm?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-mod">
            <h>modifier</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>blàth</g> can be used to modify a <a href="?xx=nouns/nouns"
                    >noun</a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples with masculine nouns – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>latha blàth</m> ann.</gd>
                        <tr>It is a beautiful warm day.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [228] [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
